    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="847"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Russian Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-08-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 7.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In reply to your note of the 23d instant,
                    I have the honor to say that this government has no objection to the extension
                    of the four months’ leave granted to Commander Rytchagow, of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Lena</hi>, for a period sufficient to enable him to recover
                    his health completely.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. B. Loomis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
